forecasting. So I don't know what sort of like the day-to-day... No, I'm speaking about like

00:48:12.080 --> 00:48:15.840
previous, like your role, I think Samsung mentioned, like, you know, your experience.

00:48:15.840 --> 00:48:25.120
Right. Yeah. It's a little tricky. Nobody really has called out our predictions in that way.

00:48:25.520 --> 00:48:35.919
I think that the only thing I can remember at Samsung was when we reported out on a marketing

00:48:35.919 --> 00:48:44.000
mix model and the results weren't what the CMO thought it would be. And so she was not as happy

00:48:44.000 --> 00:48:51.120
about the analysis done. And so she was very critical of it. Right. So, you know, I mean,

00:48:52.000 --> 00:48:56.800
nothing happened. Like, you know, at the end of the day, like they can scream and yell

00:48:56.800 --> 00:49:02.320
as much as they want, but the data is the data and data scientists can only tell you what the

00:49:02.320 --> 00:49:08.000
data says. Right. But I did learn from that experience, though, you know, I'm a lot more

00:49:08.000 --> 00:49:16.320
careful now when it comes to reporting out values to, you know, anybody, an executive team, obviously.

00:49:16.560 --> 00:49:22.959
And, you know, you just always have to remember who you're speaking to and what that means

00:49:24.399 --> 00:49:30.399
for data KPIs, because if you're going to be delivering news like that, you definitely want

00:49:30.399 --> 00:49:36.639
to make sure to show that this is based on a model. So, you know, it's not that you're giving

00:49:36.639 --> 00:49:42.719
them exact numbers. It's not a point estimate. It's, you know, it's something that has a confidence

00:49:42.719 --> 00:49:47.919
interval. So it's very helpful to show what it what you know, what the interval might look like.

00:49:47.919 --> 00:49:54.080
And so that they won't come back and say, hey, you didn't you didn't make exactly 100% this number,

00:49:54.080 --> 00:49:59.120
but then you can if you give them a confidence interval, you know, you're bound to like lie

00:49:59.120 --> 00:50:02.879
somewhere at that confidence interval. I think that's a lot more helpful than just giving them

00:50:02.879 --> 00:50:11.199
a point estimate. Thanks. Thank you, Sophia. And somehow we have reached nine minutes at the top

